mplex asteroids of the inner-Main Belt are genetically\nrelated, as they can be included into few asteroid families. Only nine\nX-complex asteroids with moderate albedo of the inner Main Belt cannot be\nincluded in asteroid families. We suggest that these bodies formed by direct\naccretion of the solids in the protoplanetary disk, and are thus surviving\nplanetesimals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Feb 2019 10:29:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-17"}
